data.content:
No codebase here — this is a knowledge question. Here's what changes for each item in .NET 10:

---

### 1. `WebHostBuilder` → `WebApplicationBuilder`
The legacy `WebHost.CreateDefaultBuilder()` hosting model is **removed**. Migrate to the minimal hosting model:
```csharp
// Before (.NET 9)
var host = WebHost.CreateDefaultBuilder(args)
    .UseStartup<Startup>()
    .Build();

// After (.NET 10)
var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);
// move Startup.ConfigureServices logic here
var app = builder.Build();
// move Startup.Configure logic here
app.Run();
```

---

### 2. `.WithOpenApi()` removed
The `WithOpenApi()` endpoint extension is **removed**. OpenAPI is now built into the framework via `AddOpenApi()` + `MapOpenApi()`:
```csharp
// Before
app.MapGet("/items", GetItems).WithOpenApi();

// After — no per-endpoint call needed
builder.Services.AddOpenApi();
// ...
app.MapOpenApi();
app.MapGet("/items", GetItems);
```
Use `AddOpenApi(options => ...)` to customize transformers if you were using `WithOpenApi(operation => ...)` to modify the operation.

---

### 3. `<IncludeOpenApiAnalyzers>` removed
This MSBuild property is **removed** from the SDK. Delete it from your `.csproj` — the relevant analyzers are now included by default.

---

### 4. `Microsoft.Extensions.ApiDescription.Client` / NSwag
With built-in OpenAPI document generation, you can now use **build-time document generation** via `Microsoft.Extensions.ApiDescription.Server`. The document is written to disk at build time, which you can feed into NSwag/Kiota/etc. Update your pipeline:
```xml
<!-- .csproj -->
<PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.ApiDescription.Server" Version="10.0.*" />
```
Then configure your client generator to consume the build-output `.json` file instead of hitting a running server.

---

### 5. `IActionContextAccessor` as singleton
`IActionContextAccessor` now has **scoped lifetime validation** enforced. Register it properly:
```csharp
// Before
builder.Services.AddSingleton<IActionContextAccessor, ActionContextAccessor>();

// After — use the built-in extension which registers with correct lifetime
builder.Services.AddHttpContextAccessor();
builder.Services.AddSingleton<IActionContextAccessor, ActionContextAccessor>();
// ↑ still works if needed, but verify — if you get runtime errors,
//   switch to AddScoped or use IHttpContextAccessor instead
```
If you only need `HttpContext`, prefer `IHttpContextAccessor` — the `IActionContextAccessor` is MVC-specific and may not be needed in minimal APIs.

---

### 6. `IPNetwork` type changed
`Microsoft.AspNetCore.HttpOverrides.IPNetwork` is **removed**. Use `System.Net.IPNetwork` (a struct available since .NET 8):
```csharp
// Before
options.KnownNetworks.Add(new IPNetwork(IPAddress.Parse("10.0.0.0"), 8));

// After — System.Net.IPNetwork uses the same constructor shape
options.KnownNetworks.Add(new System.Net.IPNetwork(IPAddress.Parse("10.0.0.0"), 8));
```
Update your `using` directives — remove `using Microsoft.AspNetCore.HttpOverrides` if it was only for `IPNetwork`.

---

### 7. `AddRazorRuntimeCompilation()` removed
Razor runtime compilation is **removed** in .NET 10. Use **Hot Reload** instead:
```bash
dotnet watch
```
Remove the `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Razor.RuntimeCompilation` package reference and the `AddRazorRuntimeCompilation()` call. Hot Reload covers the same dev-time editing scenario.

---

### 8. 401 → login page redirect on APIs
.NET 10 changes the default behavior: API endpoints now return **401/403 status codes** instead of redirecting to a login page. If you were working around this manually (e.g., custom `OnRedirectToLogin`), you can likely **remove that workaround**. If you still need the old redirect behavior for MVC pages, configure it explicitly:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddAuthentication()
    .AddCookie(options =>
    {
        options.Events.OnRedirectToLogin = context =>
        {
            if (!context.Request.Path.StartsWithSegments("/api"))
            {
                context.Response.Redirect(context.RedirectUri);
            }
            else
            {
                context.Response.StatusCode = 401;
            }
            return Task.CompletedTask;
        };
    });
```

---

**Summary checklist:**
| Item | Action |
|---|---|
| `WebHostBuilder` | Rewrite to `WebApplication.CreateBuilder()` |
| `.WithOpenApi()` | Remove; use `AddOpenApi()` + `MapOpenApi()` |
| `IncludeOpenApiAnalyzers` | Delete from `.csproj` |
| NSwag/ApiDescription.Client | Switch to build-time doc generation |
| `IActionContextAccessor` singleton | Review lifetime; prefer `IHttpContextAccessor` |
| `IPNetwork` | Switch to `System.Net.IPNetwork` |
| `AddRazorRuntimeCompilation()` | Remove; use `dotnet watch` |
| 401 redirect | Remove workarounds; APIs now get 401 by default |
